		"description": "<p dir=\"ltr\">You siphon healing from one creature and give it to&nbsp;another.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Cast this spell on a creature in response to it healing via&nbsp;any source. The target must make a saving throw against&nbsp;your spell save DC. On a failed save, you may reduce the&nbsp;hit points healed from that source by as little as one point&nbsp;or as much as the full amount that would be healed.&nbsp;Another creature within range then heals the reduced&nbsp;amount. In the case on an ongoing effect such as&nbsp;regeneration, the spell only affects the instance it was cast&nbsp;in response to, not prior or future instances. The spell then&nbsp;ends.</p>",
